U.K. Nuclear Agency CEO Quits, Joins Reliance, Times Reports

-- B y   R a k t e e m   K a t a k e y
-- 
2011-09-21T03:21:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-20/u-k-nuclear-agency-ceo-tony-fountain-quits-times-reports.html
Tony Fountain, the U.K. Nuclear
Decommissioning Authority’s chief executive officer, has
resigned and is joining  Reliance Industries Ltd. (RIL) , the Times of
London reported, without saying where it got the information.  Fountain, 50, was  BP Plc (BP/) ’s vice president of marketing and
refining before he moved to the nuclear authority, according to
the report. The resignation comes less than two years after he
joined, the newspaper said.  Manoj Warrier, a Mumbai-based spokesman for Reliance
Industries, said he couldn’t immediately comment on Fountain’s
appointment.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rakteem Katakey in New Delhi at 
 rkatakey@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
